OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1780326668
OL,3,CFour people sentenced over 'brutal and
OL,4,Csenseless' Ballymoney murder
OL,6,FFour people have been sentenced in
OL,7,Frelation to the "brutal and senseless"
OL,8,Fmurder of a man in Ballymoney, Co
OL,9,FAntrim.
OL,11,FSteven Peck, 33, who was from
OL,12,FBallymoney, was attacked on the
OL,13,FGarryduff Road on January 3, 2021.
OL,15,FHe was found on a pathway at the back
OL,16,Fof the Joey Dunlop Leisure Centre,
OL,17,Fafter a passer-by spotted him and
OL,18,Fattempted to perform CPR.
OL,26,@oD@QOUoD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,450,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1780326668
OL,3,CFour people sentenced over 'brutal and
OL,4,Csenseless' Ballymoney murder
OL,6,FSuffering from severe head injuries,
OL,7,FMr Peck was taken to Causeway Hospital
OL,8,Fbefore being transferred to the Royal
OL,9,FVictoria Hospital, where he died
OL,10,Fseveral days later without ever
OL,11,Fregaining consciousness.
OL,13,FDavid Austin, Brian McCook, Stephen
OL,14,FMcCook and Easther McCook all pled
OL,15,Fguilty to various offences related to
OL,16,FMr Peck's murder.
OL,18,FAustin, now aged 59, pled guilty to
OL,19,Fmurder and was handed a life sentence
OL,20,Fin 2023.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,450,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1780326668
OL,3,CFour people sentenced over 'brutal and
OL,4,Csenseless' Ballymoney murder
OL,6,FIn Coleraine Crown Court on Friday, he
OL,7,Fwas told he will serve a minimum of 16-
OL,8,Fand-a-half years in prison.
OL,10,FBrothers Brian McCook, 30, and Stephen
OL,11,FMcCook, 34, both from Ballymoney, were
OL,12,Feach sentenced to four years for
OL,13,Fassisting an offender, half to be
OL,14,Fserved in custody and half on licence.
OL,16,FTheir mother Easther, 51, also from
OL,17,FBallymoney, was sentenced to two
OL,18,Fyears, suspended for three years, for
OL,19,Fperverting the course of justice.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,450,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1780326668
OL,3,CFour people sentenced over 'brutal and
OL,4,Csenseless' Ballymoney murder
OL,6,FAll four sat in the dock and Stephen
OL,7,FMcCook broke down in tears as
OL,8,Fproceedings ended.
OL,10,FIn his sentencing, Mr Justice O'Hara
OL,11,Foutlined the events leading up to the
OL,12,Fattack in which Mr Peck was "brutally
OL,13,Fbeaten and left lying helplessly".
OL,15,FThe court heard Austin was told his
OL,16,Fwife had been assaulted by Mr Peck, a
OL,17,Fclaim Mr O'Hara said there was "no
OL,18,Fevidence" for, and "not a single word"
OL,19,Fwas exchanged between the couple in
OL,20,Frelation to it.
OL,26,@tD@]OUuD@aO]yD@`OUzD@IO]zD@TOUzD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,450,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1780326668
OL,3,CFour people sentenced over 'brutal and
OL,4,Csenseless' Ballymoney murder
OL,6,FThe court heard Austin then set out to
OL,7,Fattack Mr Peck, telling police "the
OL,8,Fthought in my head was to kill Steven".
OL,10,FSetting out on the evening of the
OL,11,Fincident, he wore a balaclava and
OL,12,Fbrought a knife, with the McCook
OL,13,Fbrothers, with the trio amongst them
OL,14,Fbeing armed with two metal bars, and a
OL,15,Fknuckle duster.
OL,26,@oD@`OUpD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,450,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1780326668
OL,3,CFour people sentenced over 'brutal and
OL,4,Csenseless' Ballymoney murder
OL,6,FThe pathologist found Mr Peck had
OL,7,Fsevere face and skull fractures as a
OL,8,Fresult of "multiple heavy blows to the
OL,9,Fface" from weapons or kicking, and
OL,10,Fbruises on his back "probably as a
OL,11,Fresult of kicks".
OL,13,FIn February 2023, Austin pled guilty
OL,14,Fto murder.
OL,16,FOutlining his tariff of Austin on
OL,17,FFriday, Mr O'Hara said the man's lack
OL,18,Fof remorse is "striking", having
OL,19,Fpreviously told the court he was
OL,20,F"sorry (Mr Peck) had died but was not
OL,21,Fsorry he had got a hiding".
OL,26,@pD@KOUqD@EO]rD@UOUsD@PO]zD@OOUzD@XO]|D@
OL,26,AAOU}D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
